The joint statement between the United States and India highlights the extensive bilateral partnership between the two countries. The leaders of both nations pledged to enhance cooperation in various areas such as economics, defense, energy, climate change, and global issues. They emphasized the importance of shared values, democracy, and strong economic and people-to-people ties. The statement also mentions specific achievements and agreements between the two countries, such as the signing of the India-U.S. Delhi Declaration of Friendship, collaboration on defense technology and trade, and cooperation in areas like clean energy, space, and health. The leaders expressed their commitment to working together to address global challenges and promote peace, stability, and prosperity.